    "The technology was designed to engage children in the kinds of reasoning processes that would afford connections between their app designs and related disciplinary concepts in computer science.",
    "Furtherï¿½oreï¿½ the design of the tool involved defining a set of essential actions necessary for coï¿½pleting the desired activity (Jonassen and Rohrer-Murphyï¿½ 1999) -that is, the phases of the development process that the children needed to follow to trans-forï¿½ their ideas into digital artifacts (apps).",
    "This was actualized by guiding the children to follow the basic episteï¿½ic functions related to the ML workflow for probleï¿½ solving: how to collect data relevant to solving the probleï¿½ï¿½ how to filter and clean the dataï¿½ how to label the dataï¿½ how to use those data to train a classifierï¿½ how to link the classifier results with desired behaviors (in a web appï¿½ for instance)ï¿½ and how to evaluate the ï¿½odel (Tedre et al.ï¿½ 2021).",
    "As argued by Quintana et al. (2004) ï¿½ educational technology designs should structure the functionality of the tool to support learners in observing and seeing what steps are possible, relevant, and productive.",
    "If this is properly provided, learners can also construct an understanding of the steps they need to take in their work."
